      "id": 57321898767897,
      "type": "Comment",
      "author_id": 44512844768153,
      "body": "Hi Romy Aure,\n\nGreetings from PluginHive!\n\nOur plugin works on a one plugin for one store basis.So, if you would like to use the plugin on your new client’s website, a separate plugin purchase will be required for that store. Upgrading an existing license (for example, from elephat.com) will not allow usage across multiple sites.\n\nRegarding your second question, you can use the same carrier account within the plugin across different stores, provided each store has its own plugin license. You do not necessarily need separate carrier accounts for each website.\n\nPlease let us know if you need any further clarification—we’ll be happy to help.\n\nBest regards,\nPriyanka\nTeam PluginHive",
      "html_body": "<div class=\"zd-comment\" dir=\"auto\">Hi Romy Aure,<br><br>Greetings from PluginHive!<br>&nbsp;<br>Our plugin works on a one plugin for one store basis.So, if you would like to use the plugin on your new client’s website, a separate plugin purchase will be required for that store. Upgrading an existing license (for example, from elephat.com) will not allow usage across multiple sites.<br>&nbsp;<br>Regarding your second question, you can use the same carrier account within the plugin across different stores, provided each store has its own plugin license. You do not necessarily need separate carrier accounts for each website.<br>&nbsp;<br>Please let us know if you need any further clarification—we’ll be happy to help.<br>&nbsp;<br>Best regards,<br>Priyanka<br>Team PluginHive<br></div>",
      "plain_body": "Hi Romy Aure,\n\nGreetings from PluginHive!\n&nbsp;\nOur plugin works on a one plugin for one store basis.So, if you would like to use the plugin on your new client’s website, a separate plugin purchase will be required for that store. Upgrading an existing license (for example, from elephat.com) will not allow usage across multiple sites.\n&nbsp;\nRegarding your second question, you can use the same carrier account within the plugin across different stores, provided each store has its own plugin license. You do not necessarily need separate carrier accounts for each website.\n&nbsp;\nPlease let us know if you need any further clarification—we’ll be happy to help.\n&nbsp;\nBest regards,\nPriyanka\nTeam PluginHive",
